Submission from: xia.elen.utah.edu (155.99.23.200)
Submitted by: peskin


ATACS parses for loops in VHDL, but does not seem to implement them.
These could be handled by loop unrolling.
For example, I unrolled for.vhd to produce winery6.vhd.
The latter works, but the former does not.
See the sample session below:

497 xia:examples/vhd> atacs -lv patron3.vhd winery6.vhd wine_shop.vhd
wine_example4.vhd wine_shop
ATACS VERSION 4.1
